Elem Parents--

As we look forward to Friday's Homecoming game we are equally excited for the all district pep rallied planned for Friday afternoon.

Buses will load from the elementary school and leave for Correctionville at 2:30 PM. At the close of the pep rally buses will depart from Correctionville for their normal routes. (Expect students to arrive home a few minutes earlier than normal.)

IF YOU PLAN TO PICK YOUR CHILD UP IN CORRECTIONVILLE AFTER THE PEP RALLY, YOU WILL NEED TO EMAIL YOUR CHILD'S HOMEROOM TEACHER BY FRIDAY, AT 11:30 AM.

In the event of inclement weather the pep rally will be cancelled as we cannot guarantee social distancing indoors for all of our district students and staff. If the pep rally is cancelled, routes will run from Washta at normal times and a text will be sent out to parents to notify them of the cancellation should you need to adjust your afternoon pick up times and location.

Elementary Homecoming Info‚Äî

Students will dress for the days the HS has selected

On Tuesday, Royalty will visit during lunch to wave to our students as they go through the lunch line. (Masks will be worn.)

On Friday morning cheerleaders will visit each home room to sell spirit beads. (Cheerleaders will sanitize before selling and upon entrance to each classroom. Masks will also be worn.) Beads are 50 cents each with a max of 2 beads per student.

Friday afternoon students will load their regular bus from Washta to travel to Correctionville for the all district pep rally (to be held outside on the football field) Homerooms will sit together on the field during the pep rally and buses will depart from Correctionville to their regular route. Washta Walkers will be bussed back to Washta following the pep rally (roughly about 3:40 pm)

Parents- please email your classroom teacher by Friday morning (9/11) at 10:30 am if you plan to pick your child up in Correctionville after the pep rally.

Questions? Please call our office.

post_text:
Elementary Student Drop Off and Pick Up Procedures

We want to ensure the safety of all of our students, staff, drivers, and you during our morning and afternoon pick up and drop off procedures.

Please follow the following routines:

Morning Drop Off

Please drop your student off by the library doors.
Please wait in line and do not pass any buses when dropping students off.

Afternoon Pick Up

After buses depart, please drive forward to the main entrance.
Please stay in your car if you are further than 3 cars deep. The shorter the distance to their ride, the safer our students are.
Please stay in line and do not pull in front of other cars. We will get your students out to you when you are within the 3 car distance.

We understanding waiting can be cumbersome but we are working to streamline the process while increasing safety for all.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation.

2020 Homecoming Parade will be on Thursday, September 10 at 6 pm. Line up for the parade will start at 5 pm at the Correctionville Fire Station. There will be NO candy thrown at this year's parade. Parade entries and spectators are asked to stay socially distant throughout the parade.

The 2020 Homecoming Parade route will be as follows: The parade route will start at 4th and Cedar Streets proceeding east on 4th Street to Driftwood Street turning north and continuing north on Driftwood Street proceeding east on 9th Street and ending at 9th and Hackberry Streets at the high school. (The route taken is in yellow on the map.)

A message from the Western Valley Conference:

The Western Valley Conference will be requiring the wearing of a face covering by all spectators in attendance at our volleyball events in all of our facilities at all levels. Collectively we want our students to have the opportunity to play and compete for an entire season in a safe and healthy environment.

Thank you for your willingness to cooperate with the conference guidelines.

post_text:
News from the River Valley lunchroom. We will be making some changes at both buildings to help keep our students safe during our serving time. Salad bars will be limited and open fresh fruit for High school building will not be available at this time. I will assure you we will still be providing the quaility meals we have prided ourselves on here at River Valley. I welcome to hear from any parents or students any meal modifications( medical doc required)that need to be address or any concerns that you may have. I can be reached by email tpry@rvwolverines.org or call 712-372-4656-ext1234 or voicemail

School menu on website under dining tab and prints can be made off of the document tab or I have copies available at school just let me know and Ill send with student.
First day BBQ pork sandwich
baked beans
apple sauce
peanut butter cookie
I hope and pray we get through this school year. Everyone stay safe and well.

post_text:
I‚Äôm so very proud of our baseball and softball teams tonight. March 13th was three months ago and for those three months, life as our students knew it flipped upside down. For three months we have waited to watch the kids work together doing something they enjoy. We finally got to see that again tonight. Seeing the kids having fun, being excited, and playing together brought a big smile to the entire district. We are proud of the huge step taken tonight to get back to the life we know.

WeAreRV!

post_text:
This afternoon, Governor Kim Reynolds announced an extension of school closures throughout Iowa. As a result, school buildings in the River Valley will remain closed until at least Monday, May 4.

As we have over the past few weeks, we will continue to provide meal services and learning resources for our students. We will have more details on how this will look soon. In the meantime, we wanted to update you on the governor's decision and how it will affect our schools, students and families.

Again, thank you for your patience and understanding as we have navigated this very challenging and uncertain time in the River Valley community. Please continue to practice social distancing and stay at home as much as you can to help slow the spread of COVID-19 in our community.

For the latest updates, please continue to check www.rvwolverines.org.
